So after `package_suffix`, `c->v.ss.obj` contains the register index where the class object is loaded. Then, in `be_code_setvar`, we call `setsfxvar`, which calls `free_suffix`. Let me check if `free_suffix` frees the register:

Looking at `free_suffix` again:
```c
/* release object register */
if (e->v.ss.tt == ETREG && (int)e->v.ss.obj >= nlocal && (e->v.ss.obj + 1 >= finfo->freereg)) {
    be_code_freeregs(finfo, 1);
}
```

This only frees the object register if `e->v.ss.tt == ETREG`. But in our case, `e->v.ss.tt` is the original type of `c`, which is `ETGLOBAL`, not `ETREG`. So the register is not freed!

This is the bug! When we call `package_suffix`, we set `c->v.ss.tt = c->type;` before calling `exp2anyreg(finfo, c)`. So `c->v.ss.tt` is set to the original type (`ETGLOBAL`), not the new type (`ETREG`). Then, when we call `free_suffix`, it checks if `e->v.ss.tt == ETREG`, which is false, so it doesn't free the register.

